    "comment": "Rationale: Mishima et al show that stx-1B deletion reduces the number of docked SVs and the reduces the expression levels of Munc18-1 (Fig. 1).\nRecordings of mEPSCs and mIPSCs suggest that stx-1B deletion reduces the readily releasable pool of synaptic vesicles, resulting in reduced mEPSC and mIPSC frequencies (Fig, 2). In contrast, no difference in kinetics and amplitude of evoked EPSC or IPSC between wt and KO was observed (Fig. 3). These data are explained by an increased turnover rate of vesicles in KO nerve terminals. Moreover, the levels of Munc-18 are reduced by 70%. The authors also confirm the severe inhibition of neurotransmitter release in syntaxin 1A/1B double knockouts, confirming the essential function of syntaxin 1 as one of the synaptic SNAREs in synaptic exocytosis.. Experimental description: Generation of syntaxin 1B knockout mice\nA BAC clone (37L7) containing a mouse syntaxin 1B gene was\npurchased from Invitrogen (Carlsbad, CA).\n\nElectron microscopy\nFor electron microscopic analysis of the hippocampal synaptic\nstructure, brains obtained from 7-day-old male mice were fixed\nwith 2.5% glutaraldehyde.",
